# lonloop.com — Cloudflare Pages redirect/rewrite rules.
# Syntax: <from> <to> <status>. Status 200 = rewrite (URL stays put, other
# content is served); anything 3xx would be a visible redirect.

# The World Monitor mirror is built for "/" but served from "/worldmonitor/".
# scripts/worldmonitor/lonloop-subpath.patch rewrites the paths the app builds
# at runtime, but three bundles (gdelt-intel, main, geo-map-data) bake the map
# data paths in as root-absolute string literals, so the map layer requests
# /data/countries-50m.json and /data/countries.geojson. Without this rule those
# miss every static asset, fall through to the SPA fallback, and come back as
# 200 text/html — the JSON parse then fails and the map never renders.
# Nothing else on this site serves /data/*, so the whole prefix is safe to bend.
/data/* /worldmonitor/data/:splat 200
